description._content: Catalog #: 09_01734 Title: First Lieutenant W. (Willard) Clifton Hogan Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Group of World War I flying officers standing in front of Curtiss JN-4 ""Jenny"" aircraft. Handwritten inscription ""With greetings to 'Duce Wild' Dugan. Lt. W.G. Hogan ""100% for the people - Andy Jump, Walter R. Johnson. 437 Omaha Nat'l Bk Bldg. Omaha, Nebraska"", W. Clifton Hogan (b.1880 d.1935) served in the U.S. Infantry from 1899-1901 before becoming a First Lieutenant for the Air Service in Aeronautics, serving unitl 1919.
